<br>
<br>
CDW as is should be taken over  at most 39  and many feel anything of 34 is too much.. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/blighttanksofdaoc.showUserPublicProfile?gid=craess>craess</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://media.ign.com/boards/images/icons/matrix_pills.gif" BORDER=0> at: 1/7/03 6:59:43 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#c0c0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/blighttanksofdaoc.showUserPublicProfile?gid=dajantor>Dajantor</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Journeyman</span><br>  Posts: 8<br> <font color=#000000>(1/8/03 8:08 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/flighttanksofdaocfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=74.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Piercing</span><hr size=1> I like your second plan. What I would suggest, is going full pierce and celtic-dual until level 21. You can learn how the attacking systems for the blademaster work, and then use your level 20 single-skill respec to drain your points from celtic dual and put them all into shields. This way you'll be in good defensive standing for when you get Advanced Evade, you'll have higher DEX thanks to leveling in order to block more, and you'll do just fine as a main tank for all of the grouping you'll need to do to get to 40. Then by 41 you'll have a taste of both, and can decide which you'd like to finish at, if you decide you want to specialize more than your second choice. With spellcrafting, having all of your skills around 36 is certainly useful, as long as you get the weaponstyles you need. Your only requirement is level 25 piercing for Diamondback. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#ffffff><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/blighttanksofdaoc.showUserPublicProfile?gid=colemmcbayne>ColemMcBayne</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Initiate</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#000000>(1/8/03 4:04 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/flighttanksofdaocfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=74.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Piercing</span><hr size=1> aye... I've looked over spec alot more since my First Post and my Final Spec will be...<br>
<br>
44 Piercing, 30 Parry, 34 Celtic Dual, 42 Shield...<br>
<br>
Focusing on CD over Shield untill Mini-Dings, but go up to 8 for Guard, Engage and First Stun.<br>
<br>
and Yes Piercing as a Weapon for a BM... First of so Far i've Held Aggro over All the LW Heros and Champions in any Group I've been.  Because of How Fast I Hit I out Dmg Them in the Long Wrong... i just don't do as much Initial Damage.  Not to Menchen Midgards armor is all Vulnerable to Piercing... and the only Armor Albion has that isn't Vulnerable to Piercing is Plate.  and ALL their Armors are Resistant to Slash and the only Armor that isn't Resistant to Blunt is Plate.  so Piercing makes a better over all Weapon.  Now of Course this will be able to be Fixed Some with SC, however can Never Fully Be Taken care of. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#c0c0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/blighttanksofdaoc.showUserPublicProfile?gid=skorj>Skorj</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_thatch.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Journeyman</span><br>  Posts: 42<br> <font color=#000000>(1/13/03 7:58 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/flighttanksofdaocfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=74.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Piercing</span><hr size=1> 50 Blunt, 42 Shield, 34 Parry, 20 CD BM here<br>
<br>
IMO, this is as good as a BM gets.  The class has weaker offense and better defense than a hero, so making a defensive BM only makes sense.  Even so, there's not much that's less interesting than a shield tank in RvR.<br>
